<section class="section">
  <h2>Competition Overview</h2>
  <p>
    AeroThon is a national aerospace design competition organized by SAE India,
    focused on UAV solutions for disaster-struck environments. The competition
    emphasizes rapid manufacturing, robustness, and real-world deployability.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section section-light">
  <h2>My Role & Leadership</h2>
  <p>
    I served as Captain and Mechanical Lead, leading the end-to-end mechanical
    design and manufacturing strategy of the UAV. The project required balancing
    performance with manufacturability and rapid production.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Owned overall mechanical architecture and structural design</li>
    <li>Defined manufacturing methods and material selection</li>
    <li>Designed modular, crash-resistant structures for rapid repair</li>
    <li>Integrated design-for-manufacturing principles to reduce build time</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Results & Recognition</h2>
  <p>
    The team secured <strong>1st Place overall</strong> and received the
    <strong>Best Business Proposal</strong> award, recognizing both technical
    execution and system-level feasibility.
  </p>
</section>

